I just had the worst customer experience of my life ordering from this store. I placed an order online and later received a message that my order was arriving. 15 minutes later my order was still not there. I finally received my order about 20 minutes after the message said it was arriving. After looking at my order I noticed that I was missing a pumpkin muffie and a cobblestone that I had ordered and paid for. I had to call the store 4 times to get someone to pick up the phone. The young boy that answered was not very friendly. I told him I wanted the missing items delivered. He told me that they didn't have any drivers so it would be a little bit. 10 minutes later I get a call that they are out of the cobblestones and wanted to see what I wanted to get instead. I asked for a cinnamon coffee cake. 20 minutes later a kid arrives with the baked goods but instead of a pumpkin muffie and a coffee cake I was given two pumpkin muffies. I told him it was incorrect and he said "oh well I had already left the store. Sorry." I will never order from this Panera again. I didn't spend $40 on food to not get what I asked and paid for and to be treated like my order doesn't matter.

This was my first time doing an online order/delivery at Panera Bread.  I ordered a cinnamon raisin swirl loaf, thin sliced for a small meeting that I was having at work. Delivery was quick and early but doesn't mean much if the order isn't right.  They delivered the loaf unsliced.  Called the manager, and they were out of raisin bread and had to give me a refund.  We tried to use a plastic knife since that is all we had in the office, that didn't work out so well since the loaf was overcooked (never knew a loaf of bread could feel like a football).  I suggest picking your items up from the store so you know 100% that your order is right.
